3.2 Management structure and procedures  
3.2.1.  Project management structure  
We are a research project that will run for 42 months, bringing 13 partners from 5 countries in close collaboration. The dimension of our consortium as well as the multidisciplinary and cross-functional nature of our project requires a hierarchical and robust management structure in order to ensure a smooth workflow.  
Our Project Management Team will lead the administrative and financial issues, providing support to us as the Project coordinator and the Steering Committee, which will handle the day-to-day procession of tasks. Fundamental decisions will be taken by our General Assembly formed by one representative of each consortium member. The Valorization Committee will be specifically in charge of boosting the market uptake while ensuring dissemination does not jeopardize IP protection and exploitation interests.  
Project Coordinator (CO)  
Prof. Andrea Lazzeri from UNIPI will be our Project Coordinator. He will take up the administrative/financial and technical/scientific management of our project. As CO he will act as the contact point of our project with the European Commission and will be responsible for resolving any possible administrative/financial, contractual or technical/scientific issue or misunderstanding amongst us, the beneficiaries. His responsibilities will include:  
✓ Monitoring of our project proper implementation;  
✓ Acting as intermediary for all communications between us, the beneficiaries, and the EU;  
✓ Submitting any information, deliverables and reports to the EC previously gathered from our consortium members;  
✓ Ensuring all payments are made to us, the beneficiaries, according to the GA and the CA, and organizing our project finances;  
✓ Organizing and chairing the GA and the Steering Committee meetings;  
✓ Controlling the overall project schedule and objectives maintenance, establishing and monitoring progress indicators and identifying and managing associated risk;  
✓ Maintaining regular contact with the Steering Committee members and ensuring the execution of decisions taken by our General Assembly;  
✓ Reporting our project progress and risks to the EC and our General Assembly;  
Figure 3.2 -  CEM-WAVE project management structure.  
We will be assisted by our Project Management Team, formed by personnel of UNIPI. This team will support also the Steering Committee. We are responsible for the day-to-day management of the H2020 project. We are responsible for the organization of meetings, coordination of the reporting, serving as helpdesk for queries by our consortium and any other task defined in the related WP (WP10).  
Steering Committee (SC)  
Our SC consists of the Work-package leaders (WPL) and forms the communication and decision platform concerning scientific and technical demands of our work plan chaired by the CO. The SC will provide excellence to the scientific management of our project but also reflect both an interdisciplinary and inter-sectoral approach to the overall research objectives of our project. The SC will provide strong support to the CO for the overview of our project and for monitoring progress, making strategic decisions relating both to the research and to its dissemination, and for ensuring effective communication among the participating institutions. The SC will meet at least monthly by electronic means. The responsibilities of the SC include:  
✓ Monitoring progress against our project management plan;  
✓ Reviewing and approving changes made to our project resource plan, schedules, scope, goals, cost estimates, etc.;  
✓ Making strategic decisions regarding the prioritization of our project deliverables and approving interim deliverables;  
✓ Reviewing and approving our project development strategy;  
✓ Reviewing and suggesting solutions for the issues critical to our project success;  
✓ Resolving conflicts between stakeholder groups.  
Work-package Leaders (WPL)  
In addition to our membership to the SC, WPL have the responsibility for the coordination of the technical work of the group associated with the related WP. In this role, each WPL will be assisted by all participants of that WP. The WPL will have the following tasks and responsibilities:  
✓ Monitoring of the progress of the technical work on a day-to-day basis in the work package, including scientific managing and reviewing process, identifying risks and proposing appropriate actions to the CO and the SC;  
✓ Submitting interim semestral reports to the CO regarding task progress;  
✓ Preparation of deliverables and transmission of documents to the CO and the SC;  
✓ Transmission of deliverables of us, the partners within the work package, to the CO;  
✓ Monitoring the execution and submission of deliverables in the WP to the CO;  
✓ Working together with the Valorization Committee to enhance dissemination and exploitation of results;  
✓ Deciding on scientific and technical aspects according to the WP;  
✓ Promoting communication amongst other WPL.  
General Assembly  
Our General Assembly includes one representative from each partner and is chaired by the CO. The assembly meets every six months on a regular basis, although extraordinary meetings can be required by the CO. By default, any decision can be taken by a majority of 2/3 of the voters, and to vote there should be at least 2/3 of the members present or represented. The decisions made by our General Assembly are mainly on proposal by the SC. The General Assembly decides on high-level matters relating to modifications and amendments of the work plan and the work packages, acceptance of new parties as well as the exclusion of parties, budget-related aspects, modification of the Consortium Agreement and premature completion/termination of our project.  
Valorisation Committee  
Our Valorisation Committee is the body in charge of making us take the best advantage in terms of market of our project and its results. The committee is constituted of two distinct teams, namely the Innovation Management Team (IMT) and the Communication and Dissemination Team (CDT).  
IMT - The innovation in our CEM-WAVE project will be driven by end-user needs to fully address the expectations of the industry clients. The IMT is constituted of our consortium representatives having a deep knowledge of the targeted markets and the specific environment of the industrial sectors concerned. ArcelorMittal and FM will be the pillars of our Innovation Management Team in the CEM-WAVE project, although the complete composition will be defined at an early stage of our project. The IMT will manage the implementation of the innovation cycle by pulling R&D activities towards marketable products and technologies and the creation of new business opportunities. The IMT will guide R&D activities by giving feedback to ensure that the innovation cycle leads to successful commercial applications. Key exploitable results (KERs) will be identified by the IMT and key strategic issues, such as IPR protection mechanisms, IPR sharing and routes to exploitation will be discussed extensively during meetings of the IMT. The IMT will support us, the partners who have generated KERs, to prepare business plan canvas and subsequent business plan draft. The IMT will work under the lead of Dr. Ciro Avolio of KNEIA who is the designated IMT leader in the CEM-WAVE project. He is the right person to stimulate innovation with and for industrial partners within our consortium. Our project will have also an IPR Manager from UNIPI. With extensive experience in IP management and exploitation, the manager will assist us in relation to the protection of the developed knowledge (patent search, patentability study, writing, IP valuation and contractual aspects).  
CDT- The Communication and Dissemination Team will coordinate all actions related to dissemination of our project information and communication of our project progress and results towards the stakeholder groups as well as to the general public. It will be responsible to agree upon the relevant strategy, monitor and evaluate the performed dissemination activities and their impact and adjust the established strategy accordingly. Although all partners will actively participate in dissemination and communication activities, it has been decided that members of CDT will be UNIPI (as Coordinator), POLITO (representing research/academic partners), FM (representing industry), and KNEIA (as WP9 leader). The CDT will be led by Cristina Barragan from KNEIA. She will be responsible for leading us in planning and implementing our project Communication and Dissemination activities, as well as ensuring our project reaches out to different audiences in the most effective way, and will also ensure the confidentiality of the results is safeguarded until the IP is protected.  
Advisory Board (AB).  This body consists of a voluntary group of experts who will engage with our project on an ad hoc basis according to the specific needs of our CEM-WAVE consortium and on a yearly basis at project meetings. This body has no voting rights and a confidentiality agreement will be signed with all its members. The composition of AB is set to cover the prominent experts both in academia and in industrial sectors, and its final composition and role will be detailed in the Consortium Agreement. The preliminary composition is: Byungil Yoon (DACC CARBON Co., Ltd., South Korea), Alexey Kulik (Soft-Impact Russia), Alberto Ortona (SUPSI, Switzerland), Roland Weiss (Consultant for CMCs, Germany).  
3.2.2. Meetings and communication  
Our Steering Committee will meet at least monthly on a regular basis by electronic means, in order to ensure the appropriate follow-up of our project. The Valorisation Committee will meet every three months on a regular basis by electronic means, where aspects in relation to the dissemination, and identification and management of Key Exploitable Results will be discussed. The GA will be convoked every 6 months, although extraordinary meetings can be proposed by the CO in case critical situations arise that might require it. During the meetings of the GA, the Steering Committee and the Valorization Committee will present their activities, advances and conclusions.  
